Edition:
Quote:  Various bindweeds collectively known as `convolvulus' are vigorous twiners with white or pink flowers. The most beautiful is the royal-blue morning glory that covers shrubs ..Botanical name: <i>Ipomaea learii</i>, Tropical America. Family: Covolvulaceae.
